What is Hugo&rsquo;s shortcode? A Hugo shortcode is a reusable and customizable template-like feature Shortcodes are written using Hugo&rsquo;s templating language (based on Go templates). They are placed in the layouts/shortcodes directory of your Hugo project. Create a Shortcode File Save this as layouts/shortcodes/your_shortcode.html your-site/ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ archetypes/ ‚îÇ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ default.md ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ assets/ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ content/ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ data/ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ i18n/ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layouts/ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ shortcodes/ &lt;-- your_shortcode.html ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ static/ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ themes/ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ hugo.yaml A sample shortcode is here: &lt;details style=&#34;border: 1px solid #666; border-radius: 4px; padding: 10px; margin: 10px 0; box-shadow: 3px 3px 5px #8989e420;&#34;&gt; &lt;summary style=&#34;font-weight: normal; cursor: pointer; margin-bottom: 5px;&#34;&gt; {{ .Get &#34;title&#34; | default &#34;Click to expand&#34; | markdownify }} &lt;/summary&gt; &lt;div style=&#34;margin-top: 10px;&#34;&gt; {{ .Inner | markdownify }} &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/details&gt; Shortcode for collapse section Now let&rsquo;s use the shortcode details
{{&lt; details title=&#34;Sample Text *Learn More...*&#34; &gt;}} &gt; Collapsed text {{&lt; /details &gt;}} will produce the collapsable field
Sample Text Learn More&hellip;Collapsed text
Callouts on my site I also, found out and edited the osbidian style callout. Currently it supports only important, tip, warning, and info.
{{&lt; box important &gt;}} **This is a bold line** Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Nam, omnis aliquam... {{&lt; /box &gt;}} This is the output you will get: This is a bold line
Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Nam, omnis aliquam&hellip;
Similarly, you can create for others.
This is a bold line
Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Nam, omnis aliquam&hellip;
