YouTube shortcode We can embed YouTube videos with the inbuilt YouTube shortcode
{{&lt; youtube video_id &gt;}}
The YouTube Video ID is the string of characters that appears after v= in the URL. See the video ID from the following URL
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pp6NX5lyx54{{&lt; youtube pp6NX5lyx54 &gt;}} Add quotes with Hugo &lt;blockquote class=&#34;custom-quote&#34;&gt; &lt;p&gt;{{ .Inner }}&lt;/p&gt; {{ if .Get &#34;author&#34; }} &lt;footer&gt;‚Äî {{ .Get &#34;author&#34; }}&lt;/footer&gt; {{ end }} &lt;/blockquote&gt; &lt;style&gt; .custom-quote { font-style: italic; border-left: 4px solid #ccc; padding-left: 1em; margin: 1.5em 0; color: #555; } .custom-quote footer { margin-top: 0.5em; font-size: 0.9em; color: #888; } &lt;/style&gt; To use the quote shortcode do the following.
{{&lt; quote author=&#34;Albert Einstein&#34; &gt;}} Imagination is more important than knowledge. {{&lt; /quote &gt;}} Imagination is more important than knowledge.‚Äî Albert EinsteinI will keep updating new shortcodes and tips &hellip;
